ed X-ray luminosities and gas masses\nfully covariant. Therefore, cosmological or astrophysical studies involving\nX-ray or SZ selected samples need to account for both selection effects and\ncovariance of the studied quantities with X-ray luminosity/SZ strength.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jun 2017 13:17:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Aug 2017 09:22:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-04"}
